text: how would you differentiate hyper ledger and fabric?
and which one is using a blockchain?
Fabric is a blockchain developed by IBM that falls under Hyperledger.
Jonathanlevi can probably explain better since he's worked on it so I invited him here. :slightly_smiling_face:
cool.. I'm actually talking about this in general right now if you both want to chime in

Ah, well, in general you can think of Fabric as sort of under the Hyperledger umbrella. A sub-project of sorts. We're working on proper terminology at the moment over at the Marketing Committee and Messaging WG.
It's a bit of uncharted territory at the moment with regards to terminology so we're also working with the legal department of the Linux Foundation.
